1
00:00:14,880 --> 00:00:17,920
Hi! It’s me: Nan Fah.

2
00:00:18,760 --> 00:00:20,360
I’ve just moved to Chiang Mai.

3
00:00:23,720 --> 00:00:27,080
Hey! Look where you’re going.

4
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,520
I’m so sorry.

5
00:00:36,880 --> 00:00:37,640
I’m so sorry.

6
00:00:55,800 --> 00:01:01,480
My grandfather, and his father,
and his father, and his father …

7
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:05,560
have all been doctors. My father …

8
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:07,440
What are you working on?

9
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:09,080
My Thai literature reading.

10
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:15,000
Have you done your math homework yet?

11
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:16,960
That’s next.

12
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:21,120
Nan Fah,

13
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:23,440
bring everything inside
and help me with this.

14
00:01:23,520 --> 00:01:24,280
Of course, mum.

15
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:37,520
Do you want to come play with us, Phupa?

16
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:41,040
Yeah …
Dad, can I go to play with them?

17
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:41,960
No problem.

18
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:44,680
You are so loud. Go somewhere else!

19
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:48,040
Go on!
Get out of here!

20
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:52,280
Can’t children play?

21
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:55,160
My children are studying. See?

22
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:58,200
They can’t concentrate
with all this noise.

23
00:01:58,520 --> 00:01:59,760
I only asked that they go somewhere else

24
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:04,080
Come in. Don’t pay attention to him.

25
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:13,440
Dad, please bless our business and help

26
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,320
all your grandchildren become doctors.

27
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:21,040
Hey! What happened to you?

28
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:26,000
I’ve got to go to a wedding.

29
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:29,080
Do you have anything that will get rid of these black marks?

30
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:39,080
Emotional instability,

31
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:42,000
stress and a lack of rest

32
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,760
will lead to black marks forming.

33
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,680
Hang on. I’ll get some medicine for you.

34
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:48,880
Okay.

35
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:50,200
Here.

36
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:54,960
Boil it for half an hour and let it cool,

37
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:57,880
strain it through a muslin cloth,

38
00:02:57,880 --> 00:03:01,920
dab a towel in the warm liquid, and hold it to your face.

39
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:05,200
You’ll see an improvement in 2–3 weeks.

40
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:07,520
That’s so complicated.

41
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,720
Don’t you have a cream that

42
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:12,120
I can put on and see results in a week?

43
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,880
There’s no such thing!

44
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:16,520
If you want clear facial skin, you need to get sufficient rest.

45
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,560
Also, all those sweet fizzy drinks

46
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:21,440
will age you terribly, so cut them out.

47
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:23,120
And you could end up with diabetes!

48
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:26,840
What are you? A doctor?

49
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,440
No …

50
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:34,560
Then don’t be giving out medical advice!

51
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:37,320
So what if I’m not. I’m the only one around here with any medicine.

52
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:41,120
I was just saying that although my father isn’t a doctor,

53
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:44,040
he is doing his best to continue our lineage of healers.

54
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:45,480
Keep drinking all your fizzy drinks,

55
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:48,480
but don’t come to me when you’re sick.

56
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:53,640
Nan,

57
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:58,280
look at your siblings. You have to study hard

58
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:00,880
and become a doctor when you grow up, okay?

59
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:05,120
Now the pressure is on me and my siblings.

60
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,960
Have you just moved to Chiang Mai?

61
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,800
Yes, I have.

62
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:20,040
If you want to hang with us, it’s not easy.

63
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:23,640
There is a test you must pass first.

64
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:28,280
Walk up that street to the house

65
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:31,000
with a big cactus plant,

66
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:35,240
then shout, “You bald bastard!”. Think you can do it?

67
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:41,160
You bald bastard!

68
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,520
That’s Phupha.

69
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,720
He lives across the street.

70
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:49,600
Look at him! Even his face is annoying.

71
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:52,440
Don’t run, you little shit!

72
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:55,600
I’m not bald, I’ve just not got that much hair.

73
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,400
He thinks he’s some kind of hero.

74
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:05,080
I bet Nan Fah will come running out crying.

75
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:10,200
On 1 … 2 … 3

76
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:14,600
How is that possible?

77
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:23,320
Let me see that!

78
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,200
Ow! Please be gentle.

79
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,200
I am gentle.

80
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,000
Hey!

81
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:47,920
Don’t play with them. They’re too rough.

82
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:54,400
I’ll be your friend.

83
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:02,160
Thanks!

84
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:10,680
Can we do it again?

85
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:12,640
Go!

86
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:27,480
Phu, told tight!

87
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,840
You, hold yourself together.

88
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:33,080
What the hell?

89
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:53,160
Dad …

90
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,040
Dad, please don’t leave me!

91
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:56,720
Dad!

92
00:06:57,920 --> 00:07:03,280
No, don’t cry!

93
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:08,280
Please come to the police station to give testimony.

94
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,360
Phu, please stay here.

95
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,240
Take care of him, please.

96
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,840
I will. I will.

97
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:22,520
Be strong. Your dad is at peace now.

98
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:28,400
Nothing to see here. You can all leave now.

99
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:43,680
Phu!

100
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:48,160
Nan, my dad …

101
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:50,400
My dad died.

102
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:28,760
Phu,

103
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:34,360
this is yours until you’re feeling better.

104
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:50,720
What if I never feel better…

105
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:55,280
Don’t worry. I’ll always be here for you.

106
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:59,360
This thing needs two players …

107
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:05,440
Don’t cry anymore.

108
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,080
I’ve spoken to your mother.

109
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:15,920
You’ll go  live with her in Melbourne.

110
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,640
Phu,

111
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:31,360
is that really you or am I hallucinating?

112
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:33,200
Ouch, that hurts!

113
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:34,320
Sorry.

114
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:37,880
Weren’t you going to live with your mum in Melbourne?

115
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:40,960
I’ve asked my mum to let me stay with my grandmother at the coffee plantation.

116
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:44,560
I need to get up so frigging early to get to school in time.

117
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:47,040
And another thing …

118
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:57,880
This game console needs two players, right?

119
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:03,720
Yeah …

120
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:08,720
I miss you so much, Phu.

121
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:11,880
That hurts. Are we  going to school or what?

122
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:12,800
Yes, yes, let’s go.

123
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,120
Quick, tie it up.

124
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:44,920
Go …
Phu,

125
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:47,000
What are we doing here?

126
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:48,640
It’s almost time for class

127
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:50,800
What class?

128
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:56,520
What’s the first period?
Life skills, and that’s what we’re learning here!

129
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:59,760
Ow …
It’s cold.

130
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:01,040
It’s cold.

131
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:12,080
Move! Get out of the way! Move!

132
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:18,600
Fuck, I’ve been shot by a sniper.

133
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,560
You suck!
Alright, time to study.

134
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:23,200
I’m alive. You’re dead. You go on.

135
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,480
I’ll keep playing.

136
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:27,480
That’s enough.

137
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:28,360
What’s wrong with you?

138
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:29,040
Stop playing.

139
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,320
No, no!

140
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:33,480
It’s too much.

141
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,640
I’m just going to keep on playing.

142
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:36,960
Do you know what a highlighter is?

143
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:41,040
We use it to make key information stand out.

144
00:12:41,040 --> 00:12:42,640
It will help you remember the important stuff.

145
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:45,960
Just go and read the things I’ve highlighted for you.
It will help you on the test.

146
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:50,920
If I can’t play, then neither can you.

147
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:53,360
No playing for you.
What!

148
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:55,560
Come and teach me instead.

149
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,760
Phu, sir,

150
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:15,000
did you know that test was on exactly the stuff you highlighted for me?

151
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:19,560
It was amazing! From now on I’m going to call you “Saint Highlighter”.

152
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:25,960
Or did you just sneak a peek at the test beforehand?

153
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:29,320
That might explain what happened.

154
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:37,120
Come here.
What?

155
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:42,120
The teacher told us what was going to be on the test,

156
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:44,720
but you were sleeping, you idiot!

157
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:46,680
Really?

158
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:50,120
Well, thank you anyway.

159
00:13:50,240 --> 00:13:51,960
What are you doing?

160
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:56,320
Without you my life would be a mess.

161
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:03,920
Yeah, well I’m not going anywhere.

162
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:06,680
Without you I’d have nothing to worry about!

163
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:13,480
Anyway, stop all this rubbish. Let’s go eat.

164
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:23,360
We did it!

165
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:28,640
Do you think we’ll get the jobs we’ve always wanted?

166
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:30,680
I want to open a coffee shop.

167
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:34,840
The smell of coffee reminds me of my dad.

168
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:37,400
It makes me feel like he’s here with me.

169
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:46,600
Can I ask you something?
Why did you study advertising with me?

170
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:52,080
I know …

171
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:57,440
It’s because you love me, right?

172
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:10,360
Tto, have you seen Phu?
No, not at all.

173
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:23,720
Come on! We’ll miss it.
They’re almost done.

174
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:26,360
Oh, Nan, hello!
Oh, hi!

175
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:28,920
Are you done with the graduation rehearsal?

176
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:30,280
Yeah. Have you seen Phu?

177
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:32,160
We haven’t.

178
00:15:32,560 --> 00:15:33,480
Okay, thanks!

179
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,160
Hello, Jo!

180
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:46,960
Is Phu with you?

181
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:49,640
I left with him this morning,

182
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:52,960
but he wasn’t at the rehearsals and he’s not home.

183
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:56,960
Phu’s one of those Indy kids. He goes places and tells no one.

184
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:00,720
Hold on …

185
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:15,160
I have to go see mum in Melbourne.
Take care of yourself.

186
00:16:30,120 --> 00:16:32,520
You have reached the voicemail service.

187
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:34,760
Please leave your message after the beep.

188
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:37,880
Why didn’t you let me know?

189
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:44,920
I thought we’d promised not to leave each other’s side.

190
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:13,000
Where do I begin?

191
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:23,200
Excuse me!
Have you ever seen this man?

192
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:25,000
No, I haven’t.

193
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:26,680
Have you seen him before?

194
00:17:27,840 --> 00:17:31,240
Sorry we haven’t seen him.

195
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:39,240
I’ve been emailing you for 10 years.

196
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:44,520
I’m not crazy; talking to you this way

197
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:48,000
just makes me feel a little less stressed.

198
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:51,760
The sleeping pills aren’t really working anymore.

199
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:56,080
Maybe I should take up running like you said.

200
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:05,320
I still remember you saying that
morning runs wake the body up

201
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:10,880
and leave the mind feeling refreshed.

202
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:01,240
Excuse me!

203
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:25,560
Is that all you could manage?

204
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:35,000
Come here. I’ll help. Stand up straight.

205
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:38,800
Stay still. Turn around.

206
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:46,840
You told me that all the contestants

207
00:20:46,840 --> 00:20:49,840
had to run a half marathon.

208
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:51,480
Phu

209
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:54,320
That’s why I’m trying to help you train.

210
00:20:57,960 --> 00:21:00,600
It’s only training. 2 km is enough.

211
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:05,160
No, it’s not! Look at those brand-new trainers.

212
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:07,600
You haven’t even run more than 5 km in them.

213
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:13,080
Think of beloved Dina!
It’d be embarrassing if you couldn’t even keep up with her.

214
00:21:17,120 --> 00:21:21,480
All right! For Dina …

215
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:25,800
Ouch!

216
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:28,200
There it is!

217
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:33,680
Moaning and groaning as usual.

218
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:36,360
Oh, it hurts. Argh!

219
00:21:36,360 --> 00:21:37,440
Quit acting!

220
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:38,360
Let go!

221
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:44,040
Hey!

222
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:45,280
Hey!

223
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:48,160
Hey! What’s wrong?

224
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:50,600
Are you okay? Wake up!

225
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:55,360
I really wanted to run,
but I just can’t anymore.

226
00:21:56,960 --> 00:22:00,200
Stop talking rubbish. You won’t be able to walk any time soon.

227
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:04,640
Why not?
You’re here to help me walk!

228
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:09,920
Be careful or you won’t be ready for the show.

229
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:14,440
It’s fine. I'll piggyback on you.

230
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:20,480
For real?
Yes.

231
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:21,320
Have you gone mad?

232
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:25,960
Running doesn’t seem to be helping me deal with the loneliness.

233
00:22:26,680 --> 00:22:32,040
Phu, aren’t you lonely over there in Melbourne?

234
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:40,400
Hi there!
Hi, Phu! Where are you headed?

235
00:22:40,480 --> 00:22:41,800
To delivery coffee.

236
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:44,480
Don’t forget to come over for dinner.

237
00:22:45,080 --> 00:22:46,520
Granny has prepared lots of food.

238
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:48,600
Could you take care of the customers please?

239
00:22:52,160 --> 00:22:53,520
Hi there!

240
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:54,560
Oh! the coffee is here.

241
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:55,920
Here it is.

242
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:04,360
Hang on. I heard the good news.
Congratulations on your baby.

243
00:23:04,360 --> 00:23:05,040
Thank you.

244
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:06,040
How is it going?

245
00:23:06,040 --> 00:23:07,440
It’s quite exhausting at the moment.

246
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:10,240
I bet.
I’ll bring some fresh banana blossoms with me next time.

247
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:12,880
It helps with breastmilk production.

248
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:14,280
Thank you. That is very kind.

249
00:23:14,280 --> 00:23:14,680
No problem.

250
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:15,800
Here’s the coffee.

251
00:23:16,640 --> 00:23:18,280
Thank you, Phupha.
You’re welcome.

252
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:19,240
I’ll be off now.

253
00:23:19,320 --> 00:23:20,960
Phu! Wait!

254
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:21,920
Yes?

255
00:23:23,040 --> 00:23:24,800
Do you remember Goy from up north?

256
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:27,960
Yeah. Why?

257
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:32,720
She said that after tasting your coffee, she’s fallen in love with you.

258
00:23:33,080 --> 00:23:34,400
That’s a bit much!
I know!

259
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:35,880
Did you infuse it with a love potion?

260
00:23:36,320 --> 00:23:39,440
It’s just my good looks.

261
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:40,560
Of course!

262
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:45,200
Tell her I said, “Big kisses and enjoy the coffee”.

263
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:47,560
Wait! Say that again.

264
00:23:48,080 --> 00:23:48,560
Okay.

265
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:50,240
Say it again.

266
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:50,880
Okay.

267
00:23:51,040 --> 00:23:51,960
Goy …

268
00:23:51,960 --> 00:23:56,360
